{"word":"ἀποικίζω","slug":"ἀποικίζω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀποικίζω</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to send away from home</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be settled in a far land, to emigrate</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to colonise</i> a place, <i>send a colony to</i> it, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}